── KEY FINDING ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  Mean iter_output_fraction in low-util  (<25%): 51.6%
  Mean iter_output_fraction in high-util (>=80%): 82.5%
  Difference: 30.9 percentage points

  High-util windows ARE iter-dominated. Iterations growth compounds on
  top of the cache_read weight change: more of your quota-spiking windows
  are driven by iter-bearing output.
